							<td class="pn-normal" height="24" nowrap valign="center"><a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=171&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">The Graffe's and Arcanist Hall situation</a><br><span class="pn-sub">Posted by: Bicrius</span></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td rowspan=3 valign=top align=left><a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=&amp;topic=3"><img src="images/topics/eqnews.jpg" border="0" Alt="EverQuest News" align="left" hspace="5" vspace="5" ></a></td>
							<td valign=top align=left><span class=pn-normal>For those who follow your class sites closely, this was a big deal. Some of the core members and moderators from the wizard class site <a href="http://www.graffe.com">Graffe.com</a> had split off to try to create a site that was a little more up to the times, and that was more versitle than the old Graffe's design. This site was The Arcanist's Hall (<a href="http://www.arcanist.com">Arcanist.com</a>). <br>
<br>
Although this was done with good intentions, obviously some wizards felt the wizard community start to split and tensions grew. However, wizards being the tight knit and logical selves they are, began to talk out the situation and now The Arcanist's Hall is in the process of merging back into Graffe's Wizard Compilation, bringing the wizard community back under one umbrella as well soon updating Graffe's to incorporate the superior site structure that Arcanist's had. <br>
<br>
